I now have the same issue with the following symbol missing in my custom reader op:

NotFoundError: custom_ops/librecord_reader_op.so: undefined symbol: _ZN10tensorflow10ReaderBase4ReadEPNS_14QueueInterfaceEPSsS3_PNS_15OpKernelContextE

I am using the official Docker image version 1.1.0-devel-gpu and I've already searched all shared libs in the image for this symbol.

I did not have any issues in a 1.0.0-devel-gpu image in which I manually pulled and built the TF 1.1 RC1 code (I did have a missing symbol initially, but that was solved by linking to _message.so as mentioned above).

Any ideas? I'll try to build TF 1.1.0 from source to see if that solves the issue.

body:
I now have the same issue with the following symbol missing in my custom reader op:
```
NotFoundError: custom_ops/librecord_reader_op.so: undefined symbol: _ZN10tensorflow10ReaderBase4ReadEPNS_14QueueInterfaceEPSsS3_PNS_15OpKernelContextE
```
I am using the official Docker image version 1.1.0-devel-gpu and I've already searched all shared libs in the image for this symbol.

I did not have any issues in a 1.0.0-devel-gpu image in which I manually pulled and built the TF 1.1 RC1 code (I did have a missing symbol initially, but that was solved by linking to _message.so as mentioned above).

Any ideas? I'll try to build TF 1.1.0 from source to see if that solves the issue.
